In article <2rj0i2$6q4@ugle.unit.no>, knutson@Lise.Unit.NO (Gunnar S{mund Knutson) writes:
|> A while ago here in Norway, there was quite a lot of rumors about the security of
|> cash machines(or whatever they are called in english). What happened was that
|> somone who lost her magnetic card had her account emptied just half an hour
|> later. The code we use here is a four digit number, and I think the coding
|> algorithm is called a PIN code.

Since it is not a smart card, anyone can read the magnetic tape. As the PIN
code has only 4 digits, a correlation between few cards and there known PIN
code can be extrapolated to the function which decrypt the PIN code from the
tape. Thus, anyone can read the PIN code on a magnetic card.

  --Serge
